    <div>
      <p>Hi there! üëãI'm Shutian Liang, a graduate from <a href="https://www.psy.pku.edu.cn/english/" target="_blank">SPCS</a>, <a href="https://www.pku.edu.cn/" target="_blank">Peking University</a> 
      with a bachelor degree in Psychology at 2024.</p>
      <p>
        After graduation, I work as a full time research assistant at <a href="https://www.ai.pku.edu.cn/en/" target="_blank">Institute for Artificial Intelligence</a>, Peking University</a> focusing on 
        <strong>brain-inspired AI</strong> and <strong>generative models theory</strong> under the supervision of <a href="https://www.ai.pku.edu.cn/en/info/1459/2032.htm" target="_blank">Prof. Si Wu</a>. When I was an undergraduate student, 
        I did my undergraduate research on <strong>cognitive behavior modeling</strong> under the supervision of <a href="https://www.psy.pku.edu.cn/english/people/faculty/professor/hangzhang/index.htm" target="_blank">Prof. Hang Zhang</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        I'm passionate about building novel generative models and understanding their mechanisms through the lens of geometry and physics. Though my formal training is in psychology, I am actively expanding my computer science and mathematics expertise to contribute to this exciting field. 
      </p>
      <p><strong>My motto: What I cannot create, I do not understand.</strong></p>
    </div>
